		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Windows are cotroled by the client, 100%.<br />
<br />
Your Inventory is controled by the client. Any changes are just sent back to the server.<br />
Everytime you zone, the server sends your inventory information to your client and it stores it in memory.<br />
<br />
Right now, the client won't recongize any added windows within the EQUI.xml files. Sucks, too. It's not a hard fix to put in. Matter of fact, preventing other windows would require more code than allowing them.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
